  "title": "Core Concepts of Foundations of Ancient and Colonial Burma",
  "lessonText": "This lesson explores the foundational concepts of Ancient and Colonial Burma.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• Ancient Burma, known as Bagan, was a center of culture and power.\n• The Pagan Kingdom established Buddhism as a state religion.\n• Colonial Burma was influenced by British imperial policies.\n• Key events include the First and Second Anglo-Burmese Wars.\n• The impact of colonial rule reshaped Burmese society and economy."
  }
